VALUES
(40, 9, 5, 41, 2, 9, 12, 'Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and walk?', 'Connection of Healing and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the question of what is easier to say regarding healing and forgiveness. They highlight the authority of Jesus to forgive sins and perform miracles, showcasing his divine power.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 5, 44, 3, 16, 16, 'Arise, and walk?', 'Connection of Healing and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the power of faith in relation to healing. In Matthew, the question of forgiveness and healing is posed, while Acts highlights faith in Jesus'' name as the source of strength and soundness.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 5, 42, 5, 23, 25, 'Thy sins be forgiven thee', 'Connection of Healing and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase, ''Thy sins be forgiven thee,'' highlighting the relationship between spiritual healing and physical healing. They illustrate Jesus'' authority to forgive sins and perform miracles, reinforcing his divine power.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 5, 44, 14, 8, 11, 'Arise, and walk', 'Healing and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing and authority over physical ailments. In both passages, the act of healing is presented as a demonstration of divine power, with Jesus and Paul both commanding the afflicted to rise and walk.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 5, 23, 35, 5, 6, 'Arise, and walk', 'Healing and Forgiveness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing and restoration present in both passages. Matthew 9:5 emphasizes the authority to heal and forgive, while Isaiah 35:5-6 describes physical healing and restoration of the lame.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 5, 43, 5, 17, 18, 'Thy sins be forgiven thee', 'Authority to Forgive and Heal', 'This connection highlights the authority of Jesus in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus questions the ease of forgiving sins versus healing, while in John, He asserts His divine work, equating Himself with God, which intensifies the conflict with the Jews.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 23, 43, 25, 25, 'forgive sins', 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness, as both passages address the act of forgiving sins. Matthew emphasizes the authority of the Son of man to forgive, while Isaiah speaks of God blotteth out transgressions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 40, 9, 5, 5, 'forgive sins', 'Connection of Forgiveness and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of the Son of man to forgive sins and perform healing. The question posed in Matthew 9:5 about which is easier directly relates to the declaration of forgiveness and the command to arise and walk in Matthew 9:6.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 43, 5, 21, 23, 'the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins', 'Authority of the Son', 'This connection highlights the authority of the Son in both passages. Matthew emphasizes the Son''s power to forgive sins, while John discusses the Son''s role in judgment and giving life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 43, 20, 21, 23, 'power on earth to forgive sins', 'Forgiveness of Sins', 'This connection highlights the authority of Jesus to forgive sins in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus demonstrates his power to forgive by healing, while in John, he empowers his disciples to remit sins.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 47, 2, 10, 10, 'power on earth to forgive sins', 'Forgiveness and Authority Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the power to forgive sins. Matthew highlights the authority of the Son of man to forgive, while 2 Corinthians discusses forgiveness in the context of Christ''s authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 33, 7, 18, 18, 'power on earth to forgive sins', 'Forgiveness and Mercy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness present in both passages. Matthew emphasizes the power of the Son of man to forgive sins, while Micah speaks of God delighting in mercy and pardoning iniquity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 6, 40, 8, 20, 20, 'Son of man', 'Connection of Authority and Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of the ''Son of man.'' In Matthew 9:6, the authority to forgive sins is highlighted, while in Matthew 8:20, the lack of a physical home underscores the humble nature of this identity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 42, 7, 16, 16, 'glorified God', 'Glorifying God in Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the response of the people to miraculous events, leading them to glorify God. In Matthew, the multitudes marvel and glorify God for the power given to men, while in Luke, the people glorify God for the visitation of a great prophet.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 40, 15, 31, 31, 'glorified God', 'Marveling at God''s Power', 'Both passages emphasize the reaction of the multitudes who marvel and glorify God for the miraculous works performed. The connection highlights the theme of divine power manifested through Jesus, leading to public wonder and praise.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 41, 2, 12, 12, 'glorified God', 'Connection of Marvel and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the amazement of the crowd and their glorification of God following a miraculous event. The shared themes of marveling and glorifying God highlight the impact of Jesus'' actions on the people witnessing them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 42, 17, 15, 15, 'glorified God', 'Glorifying God After Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God in response to healing. In Matthew, the multitudes marvel and glorify God for the power given to men, while in Luke, one healed individual returns to glorify God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 44, 4, 21, 21, 'glorified God', 'Glorifying God for Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the response of the people in glorifying God for miraculous acts. In Matthew, the multitudes marvel and glorify God for the power given to men, while in Acts, the people glorify God for the miraculous events surrounding the apostles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 43, 15, 8, 8, 'glorified God', 'Glorifying God Through Actions', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorifying God through the actions of believers. In both passages, the emphasis is on how the manifestation of God''s power and the bearing of fruit serve to glorify Him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 8, 48, 1, 24, 24, 'glorified God', 'Glorifying God in Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God, with Matthew highlighting the multitudes'' response to divine power and Galatians reflecting personal glorification through faith. This connection highlights a communal and individual recognition of God''s work.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 9, 42, 5, 27, 38, 'Follow me', 'Call to Follow Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus calling a publican to follow him. The act of leaving everything behind to follow Jesus is central in both accounts, highlighting the transformative nature of this call.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 9, 41, 2, 14, 22, 'Follow me', 'Call to Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus calling a tax collector to follow him. This connection highlights the theme of Jesus reaching out to those marginalized by society.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 9, 42, 19, 2, 10, 'Follow me', 'Call of Tax Collectors', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' interaction with tax collectors, highlighting their social status as sinners. Matthew is called to follow Jesus, while Zaccheus seeks to see Him and is transformed by the encounter.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 9, 41, 3, 18, 18, 'Matthew', 'Matthew''s Apostolic Role', 'This connection highlights Matthew''s identity as a disciple. Both passages emphasize Matthew''s role, first as a tax collector and then as one of the apostles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
